<h3>4.3.2 Non-conforming (geologic) layer (M)</h3>

<p>A non-conforming layer indicates a distinct change in geologic
material. This factor, like structure, consistence and bulk density, is important in terms
of water movement and retention, and root penetration. This factor has been restricted to
a strongly contrasting situation: gravel and sand underneath loam or finer. The following
table indicates the percent deduction for contrasting subsurface texture. <strong>Do not
