<h3>4.3.3 Reaction (V)</h3>

<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">Subsurface pH levels have the same kind of effects
on nutrient availability and plant growth but the impact will not be as severe as in the
surface layer (McKenzie and Nyborg, 1984). It was felt that the 20&#151;60 cm depth was
most critical and should serve as the basis for this factor. Also, this section considers
only acid soils as alkaline situations are covered under salinity or sodicity. Points are
deducted for subsurface acidity (Table 4.15) only if they are greater than the deduction
for surface acidity.</p>

